properties.description: Sets the display format for date and time values.
Sets the display format for interval values.
Sets the time zone for displaying and interpreting time stamps.
Enables input of NULL elements in arrays.
Starts the autovacuum subprocess.
Number of tuple inserts, updates, or deletes prior to analyze as a fraction of reltuples.
Minimum number of tuple inserts, updates, or deletes prior to analyze.
Age at which to autovacuum a table to prevent transaction ID wraparound. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Sets the maximum number of simultaneously running autovacuum worker processes. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Multixact age at which to autovacuum a table to prevent multixact wraparound. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Time to sleep between autovacuum runs.
Vacuum cost delay in milliseconds, for autovacuum.
Vacuum cost amount available before napping, for autovacuum.
Number of tuple updates or deletes prior to vacuum as a fraction of reltuples.
Minimum number of tuple updates or deletes prior to vacuum.
Sets the maximum memory to be used by each autovacuum worker process.
Allow accessing data from blob storage.
Enable COPY command to fetch from Azure Blob Storage.
Log level for extension.
Allow all users to access data from public storage accounts.
Number of pages after which previously performed writes are flushed to disk.
Sets whether "\'" is allowed in string literals.
Background writer sleep time between rounds.
Number of pages after which previously performed writes are flushed to disk.
Background writer maximum number of LRU pages to flush per round.
Multiple of the average buffer usage to free per round.
Sets the output format for bytea.
Time spent flushing dirty buffers during checkpoint, as fraction of checkpoint interval.
Sets the maximum time between automatic WAL checkpoints.
Enables warnings if checkpoint segments are filled more frequently than this.
Bypasses commutativity checks when enabled.
Uses the binary worker copy format.

Desired error rate when calculating count(distinct) approximates using the postgresql-hll extension. 0.0 disables approximations for count(distinct); 1.0 provides no guarantees about the accuracy of results.
When enabled, a shard move will mark old shards for deletion.
Sets the time to wait between background deletion for shards.

Sets the time to wait before checking for distributed deadlocks. Postgres' deadlock_timeout setting is multiplied with the value. If the value is set to1000, distributed deadlock detection is disabled.
Avoids deadlocks by preventing concurrent multi-shard commands.
Allows Citus to use task-tracker executor when necessary.
Enables showing output for all tasks in Explain.
Open as many connections as possible to maximize query parallelization.
Number of rows to fetch per task for limit clause optimization.
Logs distributed deadlock detection related processing in the server log.
Logs queries sent to other nodes in the server log.
Citus uses logical replication when it moves/replicates shards. This setting determines when Citus gives up waiting for progress during logical replication and errors out (in ms).
Sets the maximum number of connections per worker node used by the adaptive executor to execute a multi-shard command.
Sets the maximum number of connections to cache per worker.
Sets the maximum size of the intermediate results in KB for CTEs and complex subqueries.
Sets the level of multitask query execution log messages
Sets the maximum duration to connect to worker nodes.
Sets which SET commands are propagated to workers.
Sets the time to wait between recovering 2PCs.
Sets the number of shards for a new hash-partitioned table created with create_distributed_table().
Determines maximum number of statements tracked by citus_stat_statements.
Determines time interval in seconds for citus_stat_statements to purge expired entries.
Determines which statements to track in citus_stat_statements.
Sets the policy to use when assigning tasks to worker nodes.
Allows new local tables to be accessed on workers.
Sets the client's character set encoding.
Sets the message levels that are sent to the client.
Sets the delay in microseconds between transaction commit and flushing WAL to disk.
Sets the minimum concurrent open transactions before performing commit_delay.
Enables the planner to use constraints to optimize queries.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of processing each index entry during an index scan.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of processing each operator or function call.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of processing each tuple (row).
Sets the planner's estimate of the fraction of a cursor's rows that will be retrieved.
Sets the amount of time, in milliseconds, to wait on a lock before checking for deadlock.
Indents parse and plan tree displays.
Logs each query's parse tree.
Logs each query's execution plan.
Logs each query's rewritten parse tree.
Sets the default statistics target.
Sets default text search configuration.
Sets the default compression method for compressible values.
Sets the default deferrable status of new transactions.
Sets the transaction isolation level of each new transaction.
Sets the default read-only status of new transactions.
Enables the planner's use of bitmap-scan plans.
Enables the planner's use of gather merge plans.
Enables the planner's use of hashed aggregation plans.
Enables the planner's use of hash join plans.
Enables the planner's use of index-only-scan plans.
Enables the planner's use of index-scan plans.
Enables the planner's use of materialization.
Enables the planner's use of merge join plans.
Enables the planner's use of nested loop join plans.
Enables or disables the query planner's use of partitionwise grouping or aggregation, which allows grouping or aggregation on a partitioned tables performed separately for each partition.
Enables or disables the query planner's use of partitionwise join, which allows a join between partitioned tables to be performed by joining the matching partitions.
Enables the planner's use of sequential-scan plans.
Enables the planner's use of explicit sort steps.
Enables the planner's use of TID scan plans.
Warns about backslash escapes in ordinary string literals.
Sets the number of digits displayed for floating-point values.
Forces use of parallel query facilities.
Sets the FROM-list size beyond which subqueries are not collapsed.
Enables genetic query optimization.
GEQO: effort is used to set the default for other GEQO parameters.
GEQO: number of iterations of the algorithm.
GEQO: number of individuals in the population.
GEQO: seed for random path selection.
GEQO: selective pressure within the population.
Sets the threshold of FROM items beyond which GEQO is used.
Sets the maximum allowed result for exact search by GIN.
Sets the maximum size of the pending list for GIN index.
Sets the maximum allowed duration of any idling transaction.
Determines whether JIT compilation may be used by PostgreSQL.
Sets the query cost above which JIT compilation is activated, if enabled.
Sets the query cost above which JIT compilation attempts to inline functions and operators.
Sets the query cost above which JIT compilation applies expensive optimizations.
Sets the FROM-list size beyond which JOIN constructs are not flattened.
Sets the locale for formatting monetary amounts.
Sets the locale for formatting numbers.
Enables backward compatibility mode for privilege checks on large objects.
Sets the maximum allowed duration (in milliseconds) of any wait for a lock. 0 turns this off.
Sets the minimum execution time above which autovacuum actions will be logged.
Logs each successful connection.
Logs end of a session, including duration.
Logs the duration of each completed SQL statement.
Sets the verbosity of logged messages.
Connection log messages only show IP address of connecting host unless this is enabled. This imposes a non-negligible performance penalty.
A printf-style string that is output at the beginning of each log line.
Logs long lock waits.
Sets the minimum execution time (in milliseconds) above which statements will be logged. -1 disables logging statement durations.
Causes all statements generating error at or above this level to be logged.
Sets the message levels that are logged.
Logs each replication command.
Sets the type of statements logged.
For each query, writes cumulative performance statistics to the server log.
Logs the use of temporary files larger than this number of kilobytes.
Sets the maximum number of parallel workers than can be active at one time.
Sets the maximum number of parallel processes per executor node.
Sets the maximum number of predicate-locked tuples per page.
Sets the maximum number of predicate-locked pages and tuples per relation.
Sets the maximum delay before canceling queries when a hot standby server is processing archived WAL data.
Sets the maximum delay before canceling queries when a hot standby server is processing streamed WAL data.
Sets the minimum amount of index data for a parallel scan.
Sets the minimum amount of table data for a parallel scan.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of starting up worker processes for parallel query.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of passing each tuple (row) from worker to master backend.
Sets the maximum number of statements tracked by pg_stat_statements. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Saves pg_stat_statements statistics across server shutdowns.
Selects which statements are tracked by pg_stat_statements.
Selects whether planning operations and duration commands are tracked by pg_stat_statements.
Selects whether utility commands are tracked by pg_stat_statements.
How many server connections to allow per user/database pair. Can be overridden in the per-database configuration.
Comma-separated list of parameters that PgBouncer can ignore because they are going to be handled by the admin.
Maximum number of client connections allowed.
Add more server connections to pool if below this number. Improves behavior when usual load comes suddenly back after period of total inactivity.
Specifies when a server connection can be reused by other clients.
Maximum time in seconds queries are allowed to spend waiting for execution. If the query is not assigned to a server during that time, the client is disconnected. 0 disables.
If a server connection has been idle more than this many seconds it will be closed. If 0 then this timeout is disabled.
When generating SQL fragments, quotes all identifiers.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of a nonsequentially fetched disk page.
Enables row security.
Sets the schema search order for names that are not schema-qualified.
Sets the planner's estimate of the cost of a sequentially fetched disk page.
Sets the minimum SSL/TLS protocol version to use.
Causes '...' strings to treat backslashes literally.
Sets the maximum allowed duration (in milliseconds) of any statement. 0 turns this off.
Sets the current transaction's synchronization level.
Maximum number of TCP keepalive retransmits.
Time between issuing TCP keepalives.
Time between TCP keepalive retransmits.
Sets the maximum number of temporary buffers used by each database session.
Sets the size reserved for pg_stat_activity.query, in bytes. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Collects transaction commit time. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Collects statistics on database activity.
Collects function-level statistics on database activity.
Collects timing statistics for database I/O activity.
Treats "expr=NULL" as "expr IS NULL".
Vacuum cost delay in milliseconds.
Vacuum cost amount available before napping.
Vacuum cost for a page dirtied by vacuum.
Vacuum cost for a page found in the buffer cache.
Vacuum cost for a page not found in the buffer cache.
Minimum age at which VACUUM should freeze a table row.
Age at which VACUUM should scan whole table to freeze tuples.
Minimum age at which VACUUM should freeze a MultiXactId in a table row.
Multixact age at which VACUUM should scan whole table to freeze tuples.
Sets the number of disk-page buffers in shared memory for WAL. Any change requires restarting the server to take effect.
Compresses full-page writes written in WAL file.
Sets the maximum interval between WAL receiver status reports to the primary.
Time between WAL flushes performed in the WAL writer.
Amount of WAL written out by WAL writer that triggers a flush.
Sets the maximum memory to be used for query workspaces.
Sets how binary values are to be encoded in XML.
Sets whether XML data in implicit parsing and serialization operations is to be considered as documents or content fragments.
